We break the process into two reversible steps:

 1. Heat the liquid water from \(T_{1}=0\!~^\circ\mathrm C=273.15\) K to  
    \(T_{2}=100\!~^\circ\mathrm C=373.15\) K  
 2. Vaporize it at \(T_{2}=373.15\) K  

Let  
  m = 0.050 kg  
  \(c_{\ell}\approx4.18\times10^{3}\) J kg⁻¹ K⁻¹  
  \(L_{v}\approx2.26\times10^{6}\) J kg⁻¹  

(1) Heating the liquid:  
\[
\Delta S_{1}
=\int_{T_{1}}^{T_{2}}\frac{m\,c_{\ell}\,dT}{T}
= m\,c_{\ell}\,\ln\frac{T_{2}}{T_{1}}
=0.050\cdot4.18\times10^{3}\,\ln\!\Bigl(\frac{373.15}{273.15}\Bigr)
\approx65\ {\rm J/K}
\]

(2) Vaporization at constant \(T_{2}\):  
\[
\Delta S_{2}
=\frac{Q_{\rm vap}}{T_{2}}
=\frac{m\,L_{v}}{T_{2}}
=\frac{0.050\cdot2.26\times10^{6}}{373.15}
\approx302\ {\rm J/K}
\]

Total entropy change  
\[
\Delta S
=\Delta S_{1}+\Delta S_{2}
\approx65+302\approx3.7\times10^{2}\ {\rm J/K}.
\]
